Subject: [PATCH 2/3] Do not create .o and executables in one step

This fails when compiling with clang with the error:
  "error: cannot specify -o when generating multiple output files"

Also, there is no need to include header files when linking
---
 makefile |    4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/makefile b/makefile
index 3fc47f1..5e88c5c 100644
--- a/makefile
+++ b/makefile
@@ -9,7 +9,9 @@ all: test_mlp
 
 mlp_impl.o: mlp_impl.c
 
-test_mlp: test_mlp.cpp mlp_impl.o cast.h mlp.hpp
+test_mlp.o: test_mlp.cpp
+
+test_mlp: test_mlp.o mlp_impl.o
 
 clean:
 	-rm -f *.o test_mlp
